'''''Teaching Public Administration''''' is a biannual [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers the field of [[education]] as relating to [[public administration]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are John Diamond ([[Edge Hill University]]) and Catherine Farrell ([[University of Glamorgan]]). It was established in 1977 and is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]].

== Abstracting and indexing ==
''Teaching Public Administration'' is abstracted and indexed in [[Public Affairs Index]].

